--Boolean (logical) Operators

    ! (not)
    && (and)
    || (or)

-Not(!) operator will reverse a boolean value
     ex. console.log(!true) => false

-And(&&) takes two boolean values + will only evaluate to true if both inputs are true, otherwise return false.
    ex. console.log(true && false) => false

-Or(||) takes two boolean  values + wil only evaluate to false when both inputs are false, otherwise returns true.
    ex. console.log(false || true) => true


--Order of Opertations
    Javascript evaluates !, then &&, then ||

--DeMorgan's Law
    !(A || B) === !A && !B
    !(A && B) === !A || !B
    * used to distribute ! against parentheses *
